Vector2 Container¶

Parameters:

  • y (mixed) – y-coordinate

Copy object.

Examples

lerp(other, norm)¶

Linear interpolation between this and another vector.

Note

norm must be a float value between 0 and 1.0

Raises:

Exception – If norm not between 0.0 and 1.0
Parameters:
  • other (Vector2) – comparing Vector2
  • norm (float) – interpolation percentage
Returns:

Vector2

Examples

>>> v1 = Vector2(1, 2)
>>> v2 = Vector2(3, 4)
>>> l1 = v1.lerp(v2, 0.25)
>>> l2 = v1.lerp(v2, 0.5)
>>> l3 = v1.lerp(v2, 0.75)
>>> print(l1)
(1.5, 2.5)
>>> print(l2)
(2.0, 3.0)
>>> print(l3)
(2.5, 3.5)

normalize()¶

Normalize our vector to a length of one unit.

Returns:float

Examples

>>> v1 = Vector2(1, 2)
>>> v2 = Vector2(3, 4)
>>> v1 = v1.normalize()
>>> v2 = v2.normalize()
>>> print(v1)
(0.447, 0.894)
>>> print(v2)
(0.6, 0.8)
scale(factor)¶

Scale Vector2 by factor.

Examples

>>> v1 = Vector2(1, 2)
>>> v1 = v1.scale(2)
>>> print(v1)
(2, 4)
unpack()¶

Unpack Vector2 into x, y-coordinates.

Examples

>>> v1 = Vector2(1, 2)
>>> x, y = v1.unpack()
>>> print(x)
1
>>> print(y)
2
Returns:mixed, mixed
